<div id="review_3070121620" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3070121620" />
    <a title="Iona Sharma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1864004-iona-sharma"><img alt="Iona Sharma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1531332807p2/1864004.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3070121620?book_show_action=true">Dec 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Iona Sharma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Iona Sharma" href="/user/show/1864004-iona-sharma">Iona Sharma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1864004-iona-sharma?shelf=2019">2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3070121620" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3266289856405578785">Utterly fascinating, gripping and somehow tender, non-sensationalist collection of the author&apos;s interviews with various people injured and otherwise affected by the Tokyo subway sarin gas attacks. In an addition to the original, the author has included interviews with members and former members of Aum Shirinkiyo, the cult that perpetrated the attacks. Oddly I find these less compelling than the original interviews - in some ways they lapse into a dreary deluded sameness rather than shedding ligh</span>
  <span id="freeText3266289856405578785" style="display:none">Utterly fascinating, gripping and somehow tender, non-sensationalist collection of the author's interviews with various people injured and otherwise affected by the Tokyo subway sarin gas attacks. In an addition to the original, the author has included interviews with members and former members of Aum Shirinkiyo, the cult that perpetrated the attacks. Oddly I find these less compelling than the original interviews - in some ways they lapse into a dreary deluded sameness rather than shedding light onto the cult's motives - but the book as a whole is excellent.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3266289856405578785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

